Non-linear least squares.
There is no closed-form solution to a non-linear least squares problem. Instead, numerical algorithms are used to find the value of the parameters formula_20 that minimizes the objective. Most algorithms involve choosing initial values for the parameters. Then, the parameters are refined iteratively, that is, the values are obtained by successive approximation:
